cs.NE, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.SD 

Reasoning: 
- cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is the most likely category as the paper deals with decoding eye movement goals from local field potentials recorded through a multielectrode array in the macaque prefrontal cortex. 
- cs.LG (Learning) is also likely as the paper discusses the use of machine learning techniques to train a decoder. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another likely category as the paper deals with the development of a decoder to predict eye movement goals. 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is a possible category as the paper deals with analyzing signals recorded from the brain to predict eye movements. 
- cs.SD (Sound) is a less likely category as the paper does not deal with sound or audio signals.
